There are currently no commercial options available to return to the UK from Nigeria. All airports in Nigeria are closed to international commercial flights. Domestic flights also remain suspended. You should monitor announcements from the Nigerian authorities on the future re-commencement of domestic and international flights. If you cannot leave Nigeria at this time, see Staying during coronavirus.
UK special flights
Between 18 April and 8 June, the British government organised 12 special repatriation flights from Nigeria to the UK. There are no plans for further flights.
Your journey home: re-entering the UK
When you return, you must follow the rules for entering the UK. You:
need to provide your journey and contact details up to 48 hours before you’re due to arrive in the UK
are not allowed to leave the place you’re staying for the first 14 days you’re in the UK except in very limited situations (known as ‘self-isolating’)
See also the list of people who are exempt from the border rules.
The National Travel Health Network and Centre (NaTHNaC) also provides advice on how to stay safe as you travel by air.
If you cannot leave Nigeria
If you cannot leave Nigeria at this time, see Staying during coronavirus.
Help and support
The best way to contact us for consular assistance is to use the contact form on our websites:
Abuja contact form
Lagos contact form
If you want to call instead, the numbers for assistance are:
Abuja: +234 (9) 462 3100
Lagos: + 234 (1) 277 0780/0781/0782
The High Commission cannot provide further information or advice about departure options over the phone.
